    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "An ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/driverkit/osaction",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " object encapsulates a custom method of your driver, and the object that contains that method. When configuring your driver, you use action objects in places where the system must call your custom code asynchronously. For example, a timer dispatch source notifies its action object when the specified time elapses. Because actions execute asynchronously, store any state information your action requires in the object you specify at configuration time. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Create action objects using the method generated by the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/driverkit/type",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " macro. When you append that macro to a method declaration in your ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": ".iig",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " file, the compiler automatically generates a method with the name ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CreateAction",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "<MethodName>",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ". For example, if the name of your custom method is ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "HandleTimer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", the name of the system-generated method is ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "CreateActionHandleTimer",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". This generated method creates an action object already configured to call your custom method. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
